                  title: "Ondas Holdings Inc. Q4 2025 Earnings Call Summary",
                  snippet:
                    "A non-cash accounting charge of $82.2 million was recorded in Q4 2025 due to the mark-to-market revaluation of warrants from the October financing. The company maintains a pro forma cash balance of over $1.5 billion, providing a significant cost-of-capital advantage over subscale competitors.\nEstablishment of the ONBERG joint venture in Germany addresses the critical market requirement for localized manufacturing and sovereign-aligned defense solutions in Europe. Revenue guidance for 2026 was raised to at least $375 million, reflecting both core business strength and the contribution of recent acquisitions, which are expected to ramp up after the first quarter.\nStrategic acquisitions of Mistral, Rotron, BIRD, INDO Earth, and World View are designed to provide mission-ready technology and established customer relationships. The partnership with Palantir serves as a 'force multiplier,' providing the AI software backbone to fuse multi-domain data into actionable intelligence. Management attributes margin expansion to favorable product mix and the initial benefits of scaling revenue across a fixed cost base.\nA non-cash accounting charge of $82.2 million was recorded in Q4 2025 due to the mark-to-market revaluation of warrants from the October financing. The company maintains a pro forma cash balance of over $1.5 billion, providing a significant cost-of-capital advantage over subscale competitors.\nManagement anticipates thousands of flights per year at scale, with 50% gross margins per flight.",
