                  snippet:
                    "Record M&amp;A activity and a jump in scaling AI unicorns underscore the landscape\u2019s momentum heading into 2026. Below, we break down the top stories from the year\u2019s report, including: AI deals soften in back half of the year as funding soars ... Download the full report to access comprehensive data and charts on the evolving state of AI across exits, top investors, geographies, and more. Globally, private AI companies raised a record $225.8B in 2025, nearly double 2024\u2019s total. At the quarterly level, funding soared to $83.2B in Q4\u201925.\nRecord M&A activity and a jump in scaling AI unicorns underscore the landscape\u2019s momentum heading into 2026. Below, we break down the top stories from the year\u2019s report, including: AI deals soften in back half of the year as funding soars ... Download the full report to access comprehensive data and charts on the evolving state of AI across exits, top investors, geographies, and more. Globally, private AI companies raised a record $225.8B in 2025, nearly double 2024\u2019s total. At the quarterly level, funding soared to $83.2B in Q4\u201925.\nIn Q4\u201925, their $46B in funding represented over half of the quarter\u2019s total. Even as these companies burn through cash to meet AI development costs across hardware, talent, and energy needs, investors appear confident in their growth potential. xAI raised a $20B Series E ($7.5B in equity) in January 2026, and Anthropic announced it will raise another $10B in the same week.\nCB Insights predictive intelligence uncovers how S&P 500 companies are building their strategies for AI readiness via partnerships, deals, M&A, and hiring across the AI startup ecosystem.",
